<subSubSection pageId="236" pageNumber="841" type="conservation">
<paragraph blockId="236.[106,1312,2303,3126]" pageId="236" pageNumber="841">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[108,452,2893,2927]" pageId="236" pageNumber="841">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
Classified as Data Deficient on The IUCN Red List. The Southeastern 
<taxonomicName authority="Rat" authorityName="Rat" box="[215,417,2932,2966]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Rattus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="236" pageNumber="841" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="xanthurus">Xanthurus Rat</taxonomicName>
has a fairly limited distribution but is only known from three speciments; it might may be more widely distributed than currently known. More research is needed to fully understand its natural history, taxonomy, and conservation threats.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
